{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772134154,"nonce":"sFr8DmlxXQ3HHCm81NWawV4YNzU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87uQtqA","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/290","origin":"github"},"title":"validate_workspace.py: worktrees detected as main repos cause false version mismatches","message":"## Bug\n\n`validate_workspace.py`'s `get_actual_repos()` walks the entire `layers/` directory looking for\n`.git` entries, but does not exclude `layers/worktrees/`. Layer worktrees (created by\n`worktree_create.sh --type layer`) live under `layers/worktrees/issue-*/` and contain `.git`\nfiles (git worktree pointers). The script picks these up as \"actual repos\", overwriting the\nreal main-tree entry in the results dict.\n\n## Reproduction\n\nWith active layer worktrees for `unh_marine_autonomy` (issues #71 and #81):\n\n```\n$ python3 .agent/scripts/validate_workspace.py --verbose\n\n⚠️  Version mismatches (1):\n   - unh_marine_autonomy: jazzy vs feature/issue-71\n     at layers/worktrees/issue-unh_marine_autonomy-71/core_ws/src/unh_marine_autonomy\n```\n\nThe script finds `unh_marine_autonomy` three times (main + 2 worktrees), the last worktree\nwins via dict overwrite, and its feature branch is reported as a version mismatch.\n\n## Impact\n\n- False version-mismatch warnings whenever a layer worktree exists\n- The real repo's branch/commit is silently replaced by the worktree's\n- `make validate` fails spuriously\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n`get_actual_repos()` should skip `layers/worktrees/` entirely — worktrees are ephemeral\nagent work areas, not part of the configured workspace.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: Claude Code Agent\n**Model**: Claude Opus 4.6","files":null}]}